## 5. Rules for Claude

### When writing code

- TDD always: test FIRST, then code
- No `any`: explicit types, generics, `unknown` + type guard
- No `console.log`: use structured logger
- Follow existing project conventions
- Update this file after every feature

### When porting (porting profile only)

- Parity first — match legacy behaviour exactly, improve later
- One block at a time — close and test before moving to next
- If the new behaves differently from the old, it is a bug in the new

### When building new (greenfield profile only)

- YAGNI — build only what is needed now
- Interface first — define contracts before implementation
- Incremental delivery — smallest useful slice first

